description:
We are looking for a frontend engineer with solid foundations in one or many of our frontend stack (JavaScript, React, Redux, HTML5, CSS3, SASS) and much drive and mental flexibility to learn and interact with our backend (Java, Spring, Kafka, Oracle, Cassandra). If you think of yourself as “T\\-Shaped” or consider becoming it, you have the profile and personality that we are looking for.




 The Successful Candidate Will Become Part Of An Agile Cross\\-functional Team Of Highly Skilled And Motivated Engineers. Together With This Team And In Collaboration With Other Teams In Our Product Engineering Organization, You Will




* Discuss, define, and develop enhancement and adaptions of existing products as well as new products and services;
* Create solution designs for and deliver complete sets of functionalities from backend to frontend; the key technical focus of the role will be more on the frontend, but depending on project requirements, you can step into other technical areas;
* Work in a technically complex and sensitive environment, which will require you to build relevant functional knowledge about the products, technical knowledge about the platform’s stack and architecture;
* Keep a keen eye on application performance, operability, robustness, monitoring and failure resilience, data privacy and the security of individual services and the whole system;
* Take holistic responsibility, including ongoing functional and performance improvements, bug fixing and issue solving on the production instances of your applications and test automation as well as necessary configuration and data changes;
* Be involved in enabling and rolling out a solution to drive the business of large or enterprise partners and customers on various levels;
* Apply agile methods to organize your and your team’s work, make your planning and team performance transparent, and manage your stakeholders.


 How to Become Successful in This Role?




* To make a successful start in the Webfleet Solutions product engineering organization it will definitely help if you have a passion for software engineering, building products and tweaking systems. The most important qualification that will make you successful in the longer term, is to have a “getting things done” attitude. No matter whether it is to implement a new feature, fix a bug in production, you tackle the problem and resolve it. Also, it will be of great help if you have as many as possible of the below:
* A degree in computer science, a related field, or equivalent experience;
* Great communication skills, holistic and systemic thinking, goal\\-orientation, quality\\-focus, versatile problem\\-solving skills, an open mind as well as at least 2 years of experience in commercial software development;
* Experience with JavaScript, React, Redux, HTML5, CSS3, REST APIs
* Good foundations of UX and graphic design
* Fluency in English (written and spoken);
* A desire to work as part of an international organization and cooperate with other software engineers, system engineers, architects, product owners and external partners across multiple locations;
